      • morph

        <TTo> FunctionCompilerStates.FList<TTo,java.util.List<TTo>,TFrom> morph(Function<java.util.List<TPrev>,java.util.List<TTo>> function)
        Adds a Function to the behavior chain to change the entire list to a new list.

        The morph directive is functionally equivalent to apply, which treats the input list as a single item. But morph is aware of the list-typed output and allows list behaviors to follow immediately. Since the only difference between FunctionCompilerStates.FBase.apply(com.google.android.agera.Function<? super TPrev, TTo>) and morph is the next state of the compiler, thenMorph does not exist since FunctionCompilerStates.FBase.thenApply(com.google.android.agera.Function<? super TPrev, TTo>) can be used in its place.

        Parameters:
        function - the function to apply to the list
